1. How to add multiple users together to a group?
We can do it by using the below command-
Syntax: sudo gpasswd -M <user1> <user2> <user3> <groupname>
ex: In the below example I wanted to add “name2, name3, name4” into the group “namelist”, so I used 
	sudo gpasswd -M name2, name3, nam4 namelist
 
 
 
2. How to remove multiple users together from a group ?
We can do it by using the below command-
Syntax: sudo gpasswd -M <user2> <user3> <groupname> (here we just have to name the users which we want to keep)
ex: In the below example I wanted to remove “name2 and name3” from the group “namelist” and only wanted to keep “name4”, so I used 
 sudo gpasswd -M user4 grpname
   
 


